{
  "ir_hash": "sha256:d95820e2782470579b05172c11c630a287ab0a2f90bc99bc02b695116a27757f",
  "knowledges": [
    {
      "content": "FAPbI3 perovskite solar cells fabricated on mesoporous TiO2/FTO substrates using anti-solvent method with 2 mol% formamidinium formate (FAHCOO) added to the FAPbI3 precursor solution, 35 mol% MACl additive, Spiro-OMeTAD hole transport layer, Au electrode, measured under AM 1.5G at 100 mW/cm2",
      "content_hash": "f16006e107ab195eb4eb006dd551236d2ac689f1cc051797e18dcb22f233aafe",
      "declaration_index": 0,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::exp_context",
      "label": "exp_context",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.7
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Pseudo-halide formate anion (HCOO-) introduced via formamidinium formate (FAHCOO) into FAPbI3 precursor at 1-4 mol%; formate does not substitute iodide in the perovskite lattice but passivates surface iodide vacancy defects at grain boundaries",
      "content_hash": "71f44e2c879b280f3f4d17cccbcf3328932fccbb71ba493e1af709458c983a22",
      "declaration_index": 1,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::formate_passivation",
      "label": "formate_passivation",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.7
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "FAPbI3 PSC with 2% formate additive achieves maximum PCE of 25.59% with Jsc=26.35 mA/cm2, Voc=1.189 V, and fill factor 81.7%, under reverse scan",
      "content_hash": "f1050fa08d2f11ec0dc1c19882b0d0469d1f375599853269206edba532d79201",
      "declaration_index": 2,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::pce_25_6_pct",
      "label": "pce_25_6_pct",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.9
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Target FAPbI3 PSC certified at Newport with quasi-steady-state PCE of 25.21%, Voc=1.174 V, Jsc=26.25 mA/cm2, fill factor 81.8%",
      "content_hash": "2fa2187900ebb6613e0f4d9b692769f94692558ba1c3d87104a59ae33dcb1276",
      "declaration_index": 3,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::certified_25_2_pct",
      "label": "certified_25_2_pct",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.92
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "The Voc of 1.21 V achieved in the formate-treated cell represents 96% of the Shockley-Queisser limit of 1.25 V for FAPbI3, the highest Voc ratio yet obtained",
      "content_hash": "85c8f61a923bb13d13292f7cf5f1c42e3db66676d8514d5f54f7d23bf8f0e2a6",
      "declaration_index": 4,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::voc_96_pct_sql",
      "label": "voc_96_pct_sql",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.88
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Formate treatment results in a fivefold reduction in non-radiative recombination rate, with EQE_EL increasing from 2.2% (reference) to 10.1% (target) at injection current density corresponding to 1-sun Jsc",
      "content_hash": "6166c891181bc276d84af25c30af62ffdaa4a8799f8df9e3d226da765ae95df4",
      "declaration_index": 5,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::fivefold_el_reduction",
      "label": "fivefold_el_reduction",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.88
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "The ideality factor (n_id) of the formate-treated cell is 1.18, lower than the reference cell value of 1.52 and the previously reported best of 1.27, indicating reduced trap-assisted recombination",
      "content_hash": "40d7975668999da02d78ec43f64e7bd1f41e00a49e892cba231044d146f9d774",
      "declaration_index": 6,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::ideality_factor_reduction",
      "label": "ideality_factor_reduction",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.85
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Solid-state NMR (207Pb and 13C) measurements confirm that HCOO- anions do not substitute for iodide in the alpha-FAPbI3 lattice; the 207Pb resonance remains unchanged at 1543 ppm even with 5% FAHCOO addition",
      "content_hash": "fc7c1cbdc70ab24bf52bfbd975c9f5db526ceebfb46dd61ad8e9dbf69577f3b6",
      "declaration_index": 7,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::formate_not_in_lattice",
      "label": "formate_not_in_lattice",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.9
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "HCOO- anions passivate iodide vacancy defects at grain surfaces and boundaries by binding to undercoordinated Pb2+ sites, with the highest binding energy among all tested anions (Cl-, Br-, I-, BF4-) at I-vacant sites",
      "content_hash": "247f3429792f84ac2ae758b8e4ec24c9fd0a75c476864a928b1e27f7b6eb59db",
      "declaration_index": 8,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::formate_passivates_vacancies",
      "label": "formate_passivates_vacancies",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.87
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Adding 2% FAHCOO strongly enhances the crystallinity of alpha-FAPbI3 films, eliminating the delta-phase under high humidity (100% RH, 30C) and reducing XRD peak full-width at half-maximum",
      "content_hash": "9b7fd3f1ba3f9091fcc5ff3121207c52a04ea41d7ec9c1ac57a745056f559de0",
      "declaration_index": 9,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::formate_enhances_crystallinity",
      "label": "formate_enhances_crystallinity",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.85
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Unencapsulated formate-treated PSCs show only 10% PCE degradation after 1000 h shelf-life storage in the dark at 25C and 20% RH, compared to 35% degradation for the reference cell",
      "content_hash": "980862141f5a9cf1e5776807413022460e81a05ba6948186a794ccace929ee0d",
      "declaration_index": 10,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::shelf_life_improvement",
      "label": "shelf_life_improvement",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.83
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Target PSC retains approximately 80% of initial efficiency after 1000 h annealing at 60C under 20% RH, compared to only 40% for the reference cell",
      "content_hash": "a92429e7fd483111a3429bcbcf9f94b4f6f7e9326b9dc01127ca54b14dd4434b",
      "declaration_index": 11,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::thermal_stability_improvement",
      "label": "thermal_stability_improvement",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.83
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Under continuous 1-sun MPP tracking in N2 atmosphere, the target cell loses only ~15% of initial efficiency over 450 h while the reference cell loses ~30%, measured at approximately 35C device temperature without active cooling",
      "content_hash": "c95b0969785ea93bb11c0f219ff6b9ff235db3332dd69ca14dc4303571d063d3",
      "declaration_index": 12,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::operational_stability_improvement",
      "label": "operational_stability_improvement",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.82
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Formate-treated FAPbI3 films show significantly longer charge-carrier recombination lifetimes as measured by time-resolved photoluminescence, consistent with reduced trap-mediated non-radiative recombination confirmed by EQE_EL and SCLC",
      "content_hash": "6d85da2108d930e7963952729df27dbecdecf1885b793ceed5d7b15a1293ea79",
      "declaration_index": 13,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::carrier_lifetime_increase",
      "label": "carrier_lifetime_increase",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.84
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "Ab initio molecular dynamics simulations show HCOO- coordinates strongly with Pb2+ in precursor solution, slowing crystal growth to produce larger stacked grains; HCOO- forms hydrogen-bonded networks with FA+ at the perovskite surface",
      "content_hash": "bc7afe236aa1751e1a870ee2b2a0ab0b6b12e83335187e6248a91c46691ed25c",
      "declaration_index": 14,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::md_simulation_formate_binding",
      "label": "md_simulation_formate_binding",
      "metadata": {
        "prior": 0.78
      },
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "claim"
    },
    {
      "content": "What is the optimal FAHCOO concentration for balancing passivation effectiveness against potential adverse effects at higher concentrations, and does this optimum transfer to other perovskite compositions?",
      "content_hash": "84a4fc05c313570f92eb9d2d7037b0d1de9ef3b7cb67849e0efd4f574c1078cb",
      "declaration_index": 15,
      "exported": true,
      "id": "pvsk:pvsk_jeong2021::optimal_formate_conc",
      "label": "optimal_formate_conc",
      "parameters": [],
      "type": "question"
    },
    {
      "content": "Perovskite solar cells can achieve commercially competitive power conversion efficiency exceeding 20%",
      "content_hash": "4d29b70c694c4b3f56d48d07e077f616e92d471d2c91d7d4bb5b07e2de7c7659",
      "declaration_index": 1,
